        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A−1 A 2 × 3 rectangle has vertices as (0, 0), (2, 0), (0, 3), and (2, 3). It rotates 90° clockwise about the point (2, 0). It then rotates 90° clockwise about the point (5, 0), then 90° clockwise about the point (7, 0), and finally, 90° clockwise about the point (10, 0). (The side originally on the x-axis is now back on the x-axis.) Find the area of the region above the x-axis and below the curve traced out by the point whose initial position is (1,1).",
        "bbox": [
          0.09333333333333334,
          0.13454545454545455,
